args: It's like if good and great had kids\nor whatever. ...Goreat, maybe?
These shots are totally gonna make me\nstart bawling. That's how good they are.
And yeah, it's kinda far from the castle,\nbut I'm still happy me and Clix came all\nthe way out here for a photo shoot.
Right! Time to get my pics all organized\nand whatever! Lemme just... Wait, wuh?
There's something in the background of\nthis one. It sorta looks like... OHMIGOSH!
There! That should take care of the fiends\nin this area.
Thanks, Elisanne. And thank you\nas well, Linnea.
Oh, how wonderful it is not to live in fear\nof fiends anymore. We simply MUST find\na way to thank you!
Don't worry about it. It's our duty to\nmake sure the people here are safe.
Hey, are you the ones who beat the fiends?\nThat was awesome!
You're sylvan! Why are you living\nin this human village?!
We found this poor girl living\non her own in the woods.
She was in a right terrible state—\ndidn't even remember her real parents.
When we realized she had nowhere to go,\nwe chose to take her in and love her as\none of our own.
She's sylvan. All of you will die\nlong before she does.
This is hardly the time or place to broach\nsuch a sensitive topic, Linnea!

You can try to hide it all you want,
but she'll figure it out someday.
And you, if you don't want to be hurt, you'd
best avoid involvement with human—
Ohmigosh, bad! So bad! TOTES bad,\nyou guys! I mean, like, craaaaz—OOOF!
Ack! Sorry, girl! I was runnin' around like\nmy undies were on fire and didn't see you\nstanding there muttering or whatever.
Huh? Oh, hey there, prince dude!\nWhat a coinkidink! You out here\nenjoyin' a little chillax time too?
The ＂prince dude＂ came here with us\nto dispatch some troublesome fiends.

Whaaaat?! You don't know me?!
I TOTALLY know you, girl!
You're Li... Liiiiii... Lumbar?
...Lipstick? ...Luuuuunkhead?
LINNEA! That's it! You're Linnea!\nYeah, that's too long. Let's go with Lin.
Um...why do you know my name?
Huuuuh? Memorizing everyone's names\nat the castle is the first thing any new pal\nwould do, obvi!
Yep! I'm Nadine. Nice to meetcha, Lin!
...Why do you insist on calling me that?
Because, girl! Look, you're Linnea, right?\nLin is just, like, the first three letters\nof your name!
Ha ha! One thing about Nadine,\nshe always does things her way.
Feels like I should be offended by that...\nWait, no! Never mind! Super bad thing!\nEveryone look at this right now!
Your stone has a drawing on it.

This isn't a stone—this is my little magic
buddy, Clix! He can take pictures and
stuff, which is what we were doing back
there at that craaazy pretty lake.
But THAT isn't the point—THIS is the point:\nLook on the other side of the lake!
Dude, there are a TON of 'em out there.\nI think they're gonna, like, attack us\nor whatever?
The Imperial Army has been really\nactive lately. It's troubling.
And yet, I never thought they would\nventure into a rural area such as this.
They must be after something specific.\nNadine? Linnea? Do you mind maybe\nhelping us out for a bit?
There are a few other settlements in this\narea, and we'll need every spare set of\nhands we can get to keep them safe.
...All right. War should let me\nsee the ugly side of humans.
And since my vacation is pretty much\npoo on a stick now, me and Clix might\nas well chip in if we can!

Thanks. In that case, Elly and I will
split up and try to ambush the imperials,
while the two of you do what you can
to protect settlements in this area.
Now we're acting separately from\n{player_name}. Which means...
Lin? Hey, Lin! Where you going, girl?!
If we're protecting the settlement,\nwe should ambush the soldiers\nover at the lake.
Heeeey, I liiiike it!\nLet's go kick some soldier butt!
This whole place is, like, a snappy pic\nparadise, and I'm not about to let a bunch\nof stupid imperials ruin it for everyone.
I...don't understand anything you say.\nBut it's fine if you fight with me.

Oh, I'm gonna fight the HECK with you!
Wait, no. That came out wrong. I mean,
I'll fight WITH you. Dangit, still wrong.
...Lin? Hey, Lin! Wait up!
